title: Iresh Chamara
data: Iresh Chamara (born 4 March 1994) is a Sri Lankan cricketer.[1] He made his first-class debut on 13 March 2020, for Sri Lanka Army Sports Club in the 2019–20 Premier League Tournament.[2] He made his Twenty20 debut on 14 March 2021, for Nugegoda Sports and Welfare Club in the 2020–21 SLC Twenty20 Tournament.[3] This biographical article related to a Sri Lankan cricket person born in the 1990s is a stub.
